is\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paris Mayor\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/List_of_mayors_of_Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/List_of_mayors_of_Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 263, \"end\": 275, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne_Hidalgo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Anne Hidalgo\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne_Hidalgo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne_Hidalgo\"}, {\"begin\": 327, \"end\": 332, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.5729262840291547e-19, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In a momentous occasion, Paris Mayor Anne Hidalgo took a refreshing dip in the Seine on Wednesday, fulfilling a promise decades in the making.\", \"from\": 385, \"to\": 527, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 410, \"end\": 421, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/List_of_mayors_of_Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paris Mayor\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/List_of_mayors_of_Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/List_of_mayors_of_Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 422, \"end\": 434, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne_Hidalgo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Anne Hidalgo\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne_Hidalgo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne_Hidalgo\"}, {\"begin\": 464, \"end\": 469, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.5729262840291547e-19, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The river, long deemed too polluted for swimming, has undergone a dramatic cleanup just in time for the 2024 Olympics.\", \"from\": 529, \"to\": 647, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The city's ambitious efforts to make the Seine swimmable have finally paid off.\", \"from\": 649, \"to\": 728, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This marks a significant milestone for Paris and the upcomingGames.\", \"from\": 729, \"to\": 796, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 768, \"end\": 773, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.944217185639775e-20, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hidalgo led a group of around 100 officials, athletes, and locals in the celebratory swim, according toThe Guardian.\", \"from\": 798, \"to\": 914, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The event was met with cheers and applause as she donned a swimsuit and plunged into the river.\", \"from\": 916, \"to\": 1011, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's a dream day \\u2026 and the sun is out,\\\" Hidalgo exclaimed, completing a 100-metre crawl in the 20C (68F) water.\", \"from\": 1013, \"to\": 1125, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's sweet and wonderful and the result of a lot of work.\\\"\", \"from\": 1127, \"to\": 1186, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The journey to this point began in 2015 when the international triathlon federation suggested holding a triathlon in the Seine.\", \"from\": 1188, \"to\": 1315, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1251, \"end\": 1260, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Triathlon\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.001515072251427e-25, \"text\": \"triathlon\", \"types\": [\"Q349\", \"Q1914636\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Triathlon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Triathlon\"}, {\"begin\": 1309, \"end\": 1314, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.5729262840291547e-19, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The question loomed: could athletes swim in the Seine?\", \"from\": 1317, \"to\": 1371, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1365, \"end\": 1370, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.5729262840291547e-19, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The answer has been a resounding yes.\", \"from\": 1373, \"to\": 1410, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Tony Estanguet, president of the Paris 2024 organising committee, praised the city's efforts.\", \"from\": 1412, \"to\": 1505, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1412, \"end\": 1426, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Estanguet\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tony Estanguet\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Estanguet\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Estanguet\"}, {\"begin\": 1445, \"end\": 1455, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.856596918549655e-28, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Today we have confirmation that the Seine is swimmable and that the triathlon and marathon swimming competitions can take place in it,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 1507, \"to\": 1652, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1544, \"end\": 1549, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.5729262840291547e-19, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The river's cleanup has been a monumental task.\", \"from\": 1654, \"to\": 1701, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Swimming in the Seine has been banned since 1923 due to health risks, according toCNN.\", \"from\": 1702, \"to\": 1788, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1718, \"end\": 1723, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.5729262840291547e-19, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In 1990, then-mayor Jacques Chirac vowed to clean the river, but his efforts fell short.\", \"from\": 1790, \"to\": 1878, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1810, \"end\": 1824, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jacques_Chirac\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jacques Chirac\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jacques_Chirac\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jacques_Chirac\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hidalgo's achievement is a testament to perseverance and innovation.\", \"from\": 1879, \"to\": 1947, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1879, \"end\": 1886, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Miguel_Hidalgo_y_Costilla\", \"score\": 0.999999999992724, \"rank\": 7.1601459932704015e-12, \"text\": \"Hidalgo\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Miguel_Hidalgo_y_Costilla\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Miguel_Hidalgo_y_Costilla\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The extensive operation included constructing a \\u20ac1.4bn (R 28 378 billion) holding and treatment tank to manage stormwater and improve the wastewater network.\", \"from\": 1949, \"to\": 2106, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This massive undertaking faced numerous challenges, according toTime Magazine.\", \"from\": 2108, \"to\": 2186, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Seine had to pass stringent water quality tests for E. coli bacteria, an indicator of faecal matter.\", \"from\": 2188, \"to\": 2292, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2192, \"end\": 2197, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.5729262840291547e-19, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Only recently did the river meet the necessary standards, eliminating 75% of identified bacterial pollution.\", \"from\": 2294, \"to\": 2402, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Regular testing will continue at various points to ensure safety during the Olympicevents.\", \"from\": 2404, \"to\": 2494, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The triathlon events are scheduled for 30, 31 July, and 5 August, with a swimming marathon on 8 and 9 August.\", \"from\": 2496, \"to\": 2605, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The paratriathlon will follow on 1 and 2 September.\", \"from\": 2606, \"to\": 2657, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Competitors will set off from Pont Alexandre III, a marvel of 19th-century engineering near the Champs-\\u00c9lys\\u00e9es.\", \"from\": 2659, \"to\": 2770, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2689, \"end\": 2707, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pont_Alexandre_III\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Pont Alexandre III\", \"types\": [\"Q12280\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pont_Alexandre_III\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pont_Alexandre_III\"}, {\"begin\": 2689, \"end\": 2707, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pont_Alexandre_III\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Pont Alexandre III\", \"types\": [\"Q12280\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pont_Alexandre_III\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pont_Alexandre_III\"}, {\"begin\": 2755, \"end\": 2769, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Champs-\\u00c9lys\\u00e9es\", \"score\": 0.9938637728108773, \"rank\": 0.005341849563966386, \"text\": \"Champs-\\u00c9lys\\u00e9es\", \"types\": [\"Q34442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Champs-\\u00c9lys\\u00e9es\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Champs-\\u00c9lys\\u00e9es\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Eiffel Tower will provide a picturesque backdrop.\", \"from\": 2771, \"to\": 2824, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The cleanup operation was not without its uncertainties.\", \"from\": 2826, \"to\": 2882, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Heavy rains posed a significant risk, potentially spiking water pollution levels.\", \"from\": 2883, \"to\": 2964, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Contingency plans are in place to postpone races if necessary, ensuring theathletes' safety.\", \"from\": 2966, \"to\": 3058, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"As organisers we are very happy to be able to offer athletes the best conditions,\\\" Estanguet stated.\", \"from\": 3060, \"to\": 3161, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"But over and above that, what is at play is using the Games to speed up the transformation of the city.\\\"\", \"from\": 3163, \"to\": 3268, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Hidalgo's swim, twice postponed due to fluctuating pollution levels, came just 10 days before the Olympics' opening.\", \"from\": 3270, \"to\": 3386, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3270, \"end\": 3277, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Miguel_Hidalgo_y_Costilla\", \"score\": 0.999999999992724, \"rank\": 7.1601459932704015e-12, \"text\": \"Hidalgo\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Miguel_Hidalgo_y_Costilla\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Miguel_Hidalgo_y_Costilla\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The event symbolised hope and progress.\", \"from\": 3387, \"to\": 3426, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"French experts have identified more than 30 species of fish in the Seine in Paris, compared to just three in 1970, highlighting the river's revival.\", \"from\": 3428, \"to\": 3576, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3428, \"end\": 3434, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.7327474721346513, \"rank\": 0.22519214224530854, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 3495, \"end\": 3500, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.5729262840291547e-19, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}, {\"begin\": 3504, \"end\": 3509, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.944217185639775e-20, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The successful cleanup has broader implications.\", \"from\": 3578, \"to\": 3626, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It will help Paris adapt to the climate crisis and mitigate ocean pollution.\", \"from\": 3627, \"to\": 3703, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3640, \"end\": 3645, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.944217185639775e-20, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After her swim, Hidalgo reflected on the achievement.\", \"from\": 3705, \"to\": 3758, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3721, \"end\": 3728, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Miguel_Hidalgo_y_Costilla\", \"score\": 0.999999999992724, \"rank\": 7.1601459932704015e-12, \"text\": \"Hidalgo\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Miguel_Hidalgo_y_Costilla\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Miguel_Hidalgo_y_Costilla\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Making the Seine swimmable would also help the city adapt to the climate crisis and mitigate the pollution of the ocean into which the river flows,\\\" she said.\", \"from\": 3760, \"to\": 3919, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This historic swim marks a new era for Paris.\", \"from\": 3921, \"to\": 3966, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3960, \"end\": 3965, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.944217185639775e-20, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Seine, once a symbol of pollution, now represents renewal and resilience.\", \"from\": 3967, \"to\": 4044, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3971, \"end\": 3976, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.5729262840291547e-19, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As the city prepares for the 2024 Olympics, the river's transformation stands as a testament to what determination and innovation can achieve.\", \"from\": 4046, \"to\": 4188, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Seine River, flowing through the heart of Paris, has been a vital artery for the city since ancient times.\", \"from\": 4190, \"to\": 4300, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4236, \"end\": 4241, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.944217185639775e-20, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It has served as a crucial waterway for trade, transport, and commerce, shaping the economic and cultural development of Paris.\", \"from\": 4302, \"to\": 4429, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4423, \"end\": 4428, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.944217185639775e-20, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The riverbanks have witnessed historical events, from Roman conquests to medieval markets and revolutionary uprisings.\", \"from\": 4431, \"to\": 4549, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4485, \"end\": 4490, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Rome\", \"score\": 0.9777373083290014, \"rank\": 0.02276483134829677, \"text\": \"Roman\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Rome\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Rome\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, industrialisation and urbanisation led to severe pollution, prompting a swimming ban in 1923.\", \"from\": 4551, \"to\": 4653, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"What do you think about Hidalgo's accomplishment?\", \"from\": 4654, \"to\": 4703, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4678, \"end\": 4685, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Miguel_Hidalgo_y_Costilla\", \"score\": 0.999999999992724, \"rank\": 7.1601459932704015e-12, \"text\": \"Hidalgo\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Miguel_Hidalgo_y_Costilla\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Miguel_Hidalgo_y_Costilla\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Let us know by clicking on the comment tab below this article or by emailinginfo@thesouthafrican.comor sending a WhatsApp to 060 011 021 1.\", \"from\": 4705, \"to\": 4844, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4818, \"end\": 4826, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\", \"score\": 0.9916491928726645, \"rank\": 0.008421130362474317, \"text\": \"WhatsApp\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\", \"dbpedia\": \"http: